Business Brief -- Media General Inc.:
   Net Income Nearly Tripled
   During the Fourth Quarter
Results for the year included after-tax charges of $85.4
million, or $3.28 a share, which consisted of a $78.3 million
loss from the write-down of the company's investment in an
affiliate, Garden State Newspapers; a $5.5 million charge for
early retirement program costs; and a $1.6 million charge
accrued in connection with the planned June 1 merger of the
company's two Richmond newspapers.